{"title":"Previews","tags":["open"],"date":"2009-11-13T16:06:46Z","author":"Simon Chiang <simon.chiang@pinnacol.com>","type":"issue","content":"Previews could be implemented through the commit flag -- it's an interesting variation on previews because it would allow preview of multiple changes at once.  It may be a bit confusing, however.\r\n\r\nI like the basics, though.  Uncheck commit then add/update/remove at will.  Only the last state will be committed (although you will get dangling blobs along the way).","state":"open"}